00:12:21,836 --> 00:12:24,285
You know, to celebrate
your genuine love for her.

261
00:12:24,451 --> 00:12:25,948
Sounds good.

262
00:12:26,073 --> 00:12:28,831
And don't forget my genuine love
for par-me-zian cheese.

263
00:12:28,997 --> 00:12:31,488
Shall we say about 7:58?

264
00:12:31,613 --> 00:12:33,002
Precisely?

265
00:12:37,714 --> 00:12:39,926
Nice to see you, Zapp.

266
00:12:40,092 --> 00:12:42,699
Well, nice to see a surprising
amount of you, too, Leela.

267
00:12:42,824 --> 00:12:43,930
Is Munda here?

268
00:12:44,096 --> 00:12:46,536
Mommy's not home, big boy.

269
00:12:46,661 --> 00:12:48,905
We both know you're just
using her to get to me.

270
00:12:49,030 --> 00:12:53,106
So let's do it... right here
by the front door at 7:59.

271
00:12:57,568 --> 00:13:00,183
Leela, does your mother know
you're using her pole?

272
00:13:00,308 --> 00:13:01,406
(Grunts)

273
00:13:01,572 --> 00:13:02,852
Come on, I'm all yours!

274
00:13:02,977 --> 00:13:05,576
Have your way with me
for the next 30 seconds.

275
00:13:05,742 --> 00:13:07,590
That would be more
than enough time...

276
00:13:07,715 --> 00:13:09,455
But I can't.
I love Munda.

277
00:13:09,621 --> 00:13:10,957
I love everything about her:

278
00:13:11,123 --> 00:13:12,829
Her laugh, her maturity,

279
00:13:12,954 --> 00:13:16,199
the cold, lifeless touch
of her tentacle on my body.

280
00:13:16,324 --> 00:13:19,841
She is one juicy calamari.

281
00:13:20,007 --> 00:13:21,338
Munda:
Oh, Zapp...

282
00:13:21,463 --> 00:13:22,552
I love you, too.

283
00:13:22,718 --> 00:13:25,107
(Gasps)
Oh, squiddums!

284
00:13:25,232 --> 00:13:28,141
I've been thinking about this
for a while, and, well...

285
00:13:28,307 --> 00:13:30,246
Here in front of your
half-naked daughter

286
00:13:30,371 --> 00:13:32,228
seems like the perfect time.

287
00:13:32,394 --> 00:13:33,950
Darling...

288
00:13:34,075 --> 00:13:35,606
Will I marry you?

289
00:13:35,772 --> 00:13:37,650
Of course, I'll marry you, Zapp.

290
00:13:41,315 --> 00:13:44,761
I, uh, think a motel room
might be in order.

291
00:13:44,886 --> 00:13:46,896
Leela, here's $40.

292
00:13:47,021 --> 00:13:48,297
Mom, don't do this.

293
00:13:48,422 --> 00:13:50,913
Zapp is a selfish, womanizing idiot.

294
00:13:51,079 --> 00:13:53,082
There's no need to
call me names, Leela.

295
00:13:53,248 --> 00:13:54,471
Just call me...

296
00:13:54,596 --> 00:13:56,169
"Daddy."

297
00:13:56,335 --> 00:13:58,632
(Screams)

298
00:14:01,663 --> 00:14:03,384
{pub}Mom, if you try to marry Zapp,

299
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:05,803
